    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Stoney Nakoda, an indigenous people of Canada and the United States, particularly Montana. They are culturally connected to the Assiniboine and usage overlaps. The Stoney Nakoda Nations are: Bearspaw First Nation, Chiniki First Nation, and Goodstoney First Nation. </Note_Text>
